    "question": "Passage: \"Thailand's Open Government initiative, launched in 2019, aims to increase public access to government data and strengthen citizen participation in policy-making. Under this framework, all ministries are required to publish budget allocations, procurement records, and performance reports on a centralised online portal. Monitoring teams conduct quarterly reviews to ensure compliance. Officials who fail to meet disclosure standards may face administrative penalties. The initiative has been praised by international observers for its transparency mechanisms, though some civil society groups argue that data formats remain too technical for ordinary citizens to interpret effectively.\"\n\nAccording to the passage, what is one criticism raised about the Open Government initiative?",
