    "question": "Passage: \"Corruption in public procurement remains a significant challenge for developing economies. Research by global anti-corruption bodies indicates that between 10 and 30 percent of procurement contract values can be lost to corrupt practices such as bid-rigging, conflict of interest, and invoice fraud. Thailand's National Anti-Corruption Commission (NACC) has responded by mandating the use of an electronic bidding system for all government contracts exceeding two million baht. The system creates an auditable digital trail of every transaction, significantly reducing opportunities for manipulation. Preliminary data show that departments using the electronic system reported a 40 percent reduction in procurement irregularities within the first two years of implementation.\"\n\nWhich of the following is NOT mentioned in the passage as a form of corrupt practice in procurement?",
